Author: e-shizz <>
Date:   Sat Apr 25 14:05:44 2026 -0600

    fix(dashboard): plugin routes get proper flex context for full-height layouts
    
    - Detect plugin/override routes with isPluginRoute hook
    - Skip px-3 sm:px-6 padding on plugin routes (they handle their own)
    - Always apply min-h-0 flex flex-1 flex-col to the route container
      instead of only for /chat and /docs routes
    
    This fixes dashboard plugins that use h-full for viewport-filling
    layouts (e.g. OpenWebUI-style chat). Previously plugin routes got
    plain w-full min-w-0 which broke flex-based height calculations.

